Senior special assistant on media and publicity to Governor Darius ishaku of Taraba state, Bala Dan Abu has debunked speculation on social media that his principal is critically ill. Dan Abu, told Daily Trust in a telephone interview that it was not true as rumoured on social media that Governor Darius was hit by partial stroke According to him, Darius few hours after his return from abroad personally drove himself in Abuja. He  said that Governor Darius  also presided over security meeting in his office  in Jalingo and stayed in  his office up to 10pm. Dan Abu called the rumours mischievous and criminal. “For the avoidance of doubt my principal is well and hearty and since his return to Jalingo after a trip oversea he has been coming to his office”Dan Abu said. 2019 Elections: APC accuses Gov Darius of intimidating traditional rulers, civil servants Darius commends Buhari for approving funds for Mambilla project Kidnapping: Governor Ishaku's aide, Mijinyawa regains freedom Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin